= Action name = PCK.AUTOMIC_UIPATH.PUB.ACTION.START_JOB
= General description = This action starts a job on UiPath Orchestrator.
= Inputs = - Release Key*: Provide the unique key of the release associated with the process. E.g. 27d05882-a9kl-440a-8565-3a7298948587 - Strategy: Specify which robots from the environment will be run by the process. E.g. Specific - Robot IDs: Provide the collection of ids of specific robots selected to be run by the current process. Robot ids should be comma separated. E.g. 55577 - Number of Robots: Provide the number of robots selected to be run by the current process. E.g. 0 - Input Arguments: Provide input arguments in json format. E.g. { "key1":"value1", "key2":"value2" } - Wait for Completion: Specify whether action should wait for the job to be completed successfully. Default- Yes - Initial Waiting Time: Specify initial waiting time in minutes before the first status query. Default- 5 - Retry Count: Specify the number of retry attempts to get the status. Default- 10 - Retry Interval: Specify the interval in seconds between retry attempt. Default- 120 - Success: Specify UiPath states which end action successfully. Multiple states can be given separated by a comma. Default- Successful - Failure: Specify UiPath states will end action unsuccessfully. Multiple states can be given separated by a comma. Default- Faulted, Canceled
= Failure Conditions = * If the strategy is selected as "Specific" without specifying any Robot Id. * If Robot Ids are provided and strategy is not "Specific". * If the strategy is selected as "Robot Count" and Number of Robots is not greater than 0. * If Number of Robots is greater than 0 and strategy is other than Robot Count. * If the Job could not be completed successfully on all the robots specified within the specified time limit.
= Behavior = * Robot Ids must be provided if Strategy is selected as "Specific". * Number of Robots must be greater than 0 if Strategy is selected as "Robot Count". * If Number of Robots is greater than the number of available robots, the job will be started for all the robots.
= Return Value = UC4RB_UIP_JOB_IDS# : Comma-separated list of Job execution Ids.
= Outputs = * Return code is 0 in case of success. * Return code is non-zero in case of failure.
= Rollback = (none)
= Logging = AE logs will be displayed in the AE report.
= Example = * For 'Specific' Strategy - Release Key*: 27d05882-a9kl-440a-8565-3a7298948587 - Strategy: Specific - Robot IDs: 55577,4236 - Number of Robots: 0 - Input Arguments: {"key1":"value1","key2":"value2"} - Wait for Completion: Yes - Initial Waiting Time: 1 - Retry Count: 5 - Retry Interval: 50 - Success: Successful - Failure: Faulted, Canceled
* For 'Robot Count' Strategy - Release Key*: 27d05882-a9kl-440a-8565-3a7298948587 - Strategy: Robot Count - Robot IDs: - Number of Robots: 2 - Input Arguments: - Wait for Completion: No - Initial Waiting Time: 5 - Retry Count: 10 - Retry Interval: 120 - Success: Successful - Failure: Faulted, Canceled
* For 'All' Strategy - Release Key*: 27d05882-a9kl-440a-8565-3a7298948587 - Strategy: All - Robot IDs: - Number of Robots: 0 - Input Arguments: - Wait for Completion: Yes - Initial Waiting Time: 2 - Retry Count: 15 - Retry Interval: 100 - Success: Successful - Failure: Faulted, Canceled
